The Federal Ministry of Power has urged staff under the ministry to embrace the ongoing reforms in the power sector while cultivating good communication strategies. Speaking yesterday during a sensitisation workshop for directorate officers on level 13 to 17 in the ministry and Service Compatibility Office at the Presidency (SERVICOM) officers, held at the Power House in Abuja, the director overseeing the office of the Permanent Secretary, Mr Emmanuel Otu, said communication remains critical and key in the development of all sectors of the economy especially for service delivery. “I implore you all to take advantage of this programme to enrich your knowledge and improve on your communication skills,” he noted. The Director, Reform Coordination and Service improvement in the ministry, Mr Bernard Nwachukwu, said there was need for continuous teamwork to deliver the ministry’s mandate.